    "narrative": "Our top priority for today\u2019s slate is **Corbin Carroll**, who stands as our clear anchor with an elite score of 85.93. Facing Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez, **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a massive 19% boost in SP skill projection and, critically, the slow delivery of M\u00e1rquez, which provides a high-leverage environment for his elite speed in our pursuit of scarce stolen bases. Following him, **Seiya Suzuki** (69.55) and **Brice Turang** (66.73) provide the high-floor production we need. **Seiya Suzuki** benefits from a favorable matchup against Roki Sasaki (xERA 5.52) and beneficial wind conditions, while **Brice Turang** remains a staple in our lineup due to his premium lead-off spot and the dynamic platoon advantage against Mitch Keller. **Trevor Story** also earns a strong recommendation (63.84) thanks to a significant 16% park factor bump that elevates his scoring ceiling despite a moderate matchup.\n\nThe bench decision process was particularly tight at the bottom of the order, where **Alex Freeland** (49.73) fell just short of a starting berth. While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility and positive wind indicators, the heavy penalty associated with his projected #9 spot in the order kept him behind the more consistent projected output of **Max Muncy** and **Tyler Soderstrom**. Meanwhile, **Austin Riley** (44.51) was relegated to the pine due to the brutal matchup against Zack Wheeler, whose 2.73 xERA serves as a prohibitive floor-killer for our daily efficiency goals. \n\nInvestors should remain vigilant regarding our two rain-risk designations. **Luis Campusano** is currently flagged with a 36% rain risk; while he sits at a marginal 44.92, any shift in the weather or a late-breaking lineup announcement could render him a total liability. Furthermore, **Corbin Carroll** shares that same 36% rain risk, though his massive scoring upside makes him a lock regardless of the volatility. We are monitoring **Dalton Rushing**, **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **James Wood**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, and **Josh Naylor** for official lineup confirmation, as their scores are highly sensitive to their specific slotting in the batting order. We are proceeding without **Gabriel Moreno**, who remains on the IL, keeping our depth limited as we navigate these mid-week matchups.",
